    think='Now I have enough information to compile a comprehensive review repor
t. Let me summarize the key issues I\'ve found:\n\n**Blocking Issues:**\n1. **UU
ID v4 validation on UUID v7 fields** - `MarkAsReadDto` and `SendMessageDto` use 
`@IsUUID("4")` but IDs are generated with `uuidv7()`. This will cause validation
failures for valid IDs.\n\n**Major Issues:**\n1. **OpenAPI MessageDto.type enum 
missing "system"** - The API contract (`docs/api-contracts/im.yaml`) defines `Me
ssageDto.type` enum as `[text, image]` but the backend creates `system` messages
. This breaks contract sync.\n2. **Missing system message fallback in getMessage
s** - PRD requires: "打开会话时，若数据库中无系统消息记录，后端自动插入一条 type
= \'system\' 的消息作为欢迎语。" The `getMessages` method does NOT implement thi
s fallback. There\'s a race condition where the client might open a conversation
before the async event handler creates the system message.\n3. **MatchingModule 
does not import ImModule** - PR description claims it does, but it doesn\'t. Whi
le EventEmitter decoupling means it might not be strictly necessary, the PR desc
ription is inaccurate and if there were direct service dependencies, this would 
be a problem. Actually, looking again, MatchingService doesn\'t directly call Im
Service - it uses EventEmitter. So this is more of a documentation inconsistency
than a code bug. But the PR description is misleading.\n4. **BDD push notificati
on step is essentially a placeholder** - The `im_real_time_message_delivery.step
s.js` has a TODO step for push notifications with `assert.ok(true, ...)`. Accord
ing to testing.md, step definitions should not be empty implementations. However
, the step has a detailed comment explaining why. This is borderline.\n\nWait, l
et me re-evaluate the Major issues. I can only have up to 5 Blocking + Major tot
al. Let me pick the most important ones.\n\nActually, looking at the UUID issue 
more carefully:\n- `SendMessageDto.conversation_id` uses `@IsUUID("4")` - conver
sation IDs are created with `uuidv7()` in `matching.service.ts` (line 442: `id: 
uuidv7()`). So this IS a problem.\n- `MarkAsReadDto.last_message_id` uses `@IsUU
ID("4")` - message IDs are created with `uuidv7()` in `im.service.ts` (line 108:
`id: uuidv7()`). So this IS a problem.\n- `MarkAsReadDto.conversation_id` uses `
@IsUUID("4")` - same issue.\n\nThis is definitely Blocking.\n\nFor Major issues:
\n1. OpenAPI contract `MessageDto.type` missing `system` - Major (contract sync)
\n2. Missing system message auto-insertion fallback in `getMessages` - Major (PR
D requirement not met)\n3. `MatchingModule` missing `ImModule` import when PR cl
aims it was added - I\'ll classify this as Minor since EventEmitter decoupling m
akes it work without the import. The real issue is PR description inaccuracy.\n4
. BDD push notification placeholder - I\'ll classify this as Minor since it\'s e
xplicitly documented as tech debt.\n\nWait, let me re-read the PRD requirement a
bout system messages:\n"打开会话时，若数据库中无系统消息记录，后端自动插入一条 t
ype = \'system\' 的消息作为欢迎语。"\n\nThis is a clear PRD requirement. The cur
rent implementation only creates the system message asynchronously via EventEmit
ter after match creation. If that fails or is delayed, opening the conversation 
will show an empty chat without the welcome message. The `getMessages` service m
ethod should have a fallback to auto-insert the welcome message if the conversat
ion has no messages. This is a functional gap.\n\nAnother potential issue: `Matc
hingModule` doesn\'t import `ImModule`, but `ImModule` exports `ImService` and `
ImGateway`. Since `MatchingService` uses `EventEmitter2` to emit events and `ImS
